Description: Up for auction is this very nice 1999 American Deluxe HSS Stratocaster. This guitar is in Very Good condition. There are no significant flaws to the Transparent Red finish and only a few minor mars or dings, none of which can be seen except under close physical examination. There is some very light scratching above the pick guard towards the upper bout, and some belt rash on the back. Everything on this guitar is original equipment. To start, this guitar is an HSS or Humbucker, Single coil, Single Coil pickup configuration. The pick guard and Tremolo Spring Cover are 3 ply white. The controls and pickups are white. Standard is the Fender 5 way pick up selector switch. The pickups are original Fender Noiseless. The bridge is the fully adjustable solid metal bridge sections model as are used on the current American Elite series of Stratocasters, with a pop in tremolo bar and 2 point tremolo tailpiece. This particular guitar has a 9.5" radius adjustable maple neck with rolled edges, highly detailed and finished medium frets and a beautiful dark Rosewood fingerboard with Abalone dot fret marker inlays. There is no discernible fret wear. It has Fender's MicroTIlt adjustment access in the heel plate. The nut is a Fender LSR roller nut. There is no fret wear. Up top, the tuning gears are polished locking machines. This guitar comes complete with Tremolo bar, Polishing Cloth, Neck, Bridge and heel Allen Adjusting wrenches, and a deluxe Fender Gig bag. And certainly, please feel free to ask any questions and good luck!
